<h2>Expert Tips</h2>

<ol>
<li>Match wine intensity to food intensity - lighter Merlots with delicate dishes, bolder versions with rich preparations</li>
<li>Consider the sauce as much as the protein when pairing - mushroom sauces almost always work with Merlot</li>
<li>Serve Merlot slightly below room temperature (62-65°F) to maintain its fresh fruit character</li>
<li>Decant older Merlots for 30-60 minutes, but younger wines can be enjoyed immediately</li>
<li>Avoid pairing Merlot with very spicy foods - the alcohol will amplify heat perception</li>
<li>Choose cooking wines you'd drink - if you cook with Merlot, use a bottle you'd enjoy on its own</li>
<li>Consider regional food pairings - French Merlot with French cuisine, California Merlot with American dishes</li>
<li>Don't overthink it - Merlot's food-friendly nature means most pairings will work reasonably well</li>
</ol>

